			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2010</a> paper:</span><br><i>Translator Generation Using ART (Tools Paper)</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/AdrianJohnstone.html">Adrian Johnstone</a>, <a href="../profile/ElizabethScott.html">Elizabeth Scott</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_20">10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_20</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagM">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> The paper is about translator/parser generation and staged grammar-to-parser compilation.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> ART is a concrete tool that generates parsers/tree-walkers and supports modular grammar engineering.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> It addresses modularization/composition of grammar modules and staged transformation pipelines.
</li></ul></li></ul>
